text: Faristenia nemoriella is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It is found in the Russian Far East.Faristenia at funet The wingspan is 17–19 mm. The forewings are grey with two large dark costal spots, five longitudinal dark strokes and several small dots along the apex and external margin. The hindwings are grey.Far East.
